<p>With this interpretation in mind, the -3 weight on edge C-&gt;A could me=
an that the fuel cost is $5 driving from C to A, and that we get paid $8 fo=
r picking up packages in C and delivering them in A. So we end up earning $=
3 more than we spend. Therefore, a total of $2 can be made by driving the d=
elivery route D-&gt;E-&gt;B-&gt;C-&gt;A in our graph above.</p>
