<h2>Returning The Paths from The Bellman-Ford Algorithm</h2>
<p>We are currently finding the total weight of the the shortest paths, so =
that for example "Distance from D to A: -2" is a result from running the Be=
llman-Ford algorithm.</p>
<p>But by recording the predecessor of each vertex whenever an edge is rela=
xed, we can use that later in our code to print the result including the ac=
tual shortest paths. This means we can give more information in our result,=
 with the actual path in addition to the path weight: "D-&gt;E-&gt;B-&gt;C-=
&gt;A, Distance: -2".</p>
<p>This last code example is the complete code for the Bellman-Ford algorit=
